Source: splitdnsd
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: gutschke <gutschke@users.noreply.github.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), golang-1.24 | golang-go (>= 2:1.24~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/gutschke/splitdns
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: splitdnsd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, adduser
Recommends: splitdns-notify (= ${binary:Version}), ieee-data
Description: split-horizon DNS resolver with optional Cloudflare mirror
 splitdnsd is a lightweight authoritative and forwarding DNS resolver for a
 trusted LAN. It serves *.local names from mDNS, answers reverse (PTR) zones,
 forwards other queries over DNS-over-TLS, and can optionally mirror
 Cloudflare-hosted zones (read-only) and perform guarded, opt-in dynamic-DNS
 write-back.
 .
 The query hot path performs no external I/O (it reads an atomically published
 snapshot), so a slow or unreachable upstream cannot wedge resolution.
 .
 Configuration is not shipped: copy the example from /usr/share/doc/splitdnsd/
 to /etc/splitdns/splitdnsd.toml and edit it. See splitdns.conf(5).

Package: splitdns-notify
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: mDNS hostname announcer for splitdnsd
 splitdns-notify sends authoritative multicast-DNS responses to announce a
 host's name and addresses, prompting a splitdnsd resolver to refresh its view
 of the LAN (and, where enabled, its guarded dynamic-DNS write-back).
 .
 It is a small static helper with no runtime dependencies and ships neither the
 server binary nor any service, so it is safe to install on hosts that should
 announce themselves to — but never run — splitdnsd. See splitdns-notify(8).

Package: splitdnsd-selfbuild
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, init-system-helpers (>= 1.54~),
 golang-1.24 | golang-go (>= 2:1.24~), default-mta | mail-transport-agent, dpkg-repack
Recommends: splitdnsd, splitdns-notify, bind9-dnsutils | dnsutils, debsecan
Description: unattended security self-rebuild for splitdnsd
 splitdnsd ships as a static Go binary, so its dependencies (the Go
 standard library and vendored libraries) are baked in at build time and
 update only on a rebuild — unlike a dynamically linked program, which
 picks up a patched shared library automatically on apt dist-upgrade.
 This package closes that gap: it ships the source and rebuilds
 splitdnsd/splitdns-notify against the current apt Go toolchain whenever
 it changes (after apt runs, and weekly as a backstop), installing only
 after config-validation and a DNS health check, with automatic rollback
 and email-on-failure (via the system mail-transport-agent; install e.g.
 msmtp-mta, no MTA is hard-coded).
 .
 It does NOT hard-depend on splitdnsd/splitdns-notify, so any combination
 of the three packages is a valid install; if either has been removed,
 the self-build reinstalls it.
